    <intervention_type>Procedure</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Intervention group_MRA</intervention_name>
    <description>Tidal Volume (Vt) =6-8 mL/kg of predicted body weight (PBW), Peep=8 cmH2O, recruitment maneuvers=30cm H2O every 30 min after intubation (except during CPB), after any disconnection and at the admission in ICU.
Recruitment maneuvers are performed in accordance with the surgical team an if SAP≥90 mmHg or MAP≥65 mmHg.
Ventilation is maintained during CPB Vt=2.5 mL/kg, Peep= 5 cmH2O</description>
